{
  "stem": "18102.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 25.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And now he left again for the forests of Lithuania outside of Kaunas.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Again, he was in the company of others who were running, and for one reason or other didn't trust the-- the Russians.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was there in Kaunas, in the forests of Kaunas, that rumors came to him that the General Council of Japan, Sugihara, might be issuing visas to enter-- a transit visa, transit papers, in effect-- to enter Japan.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "No one knew if you could leave anyway, because to leave a Russian occupied territory, you needed permission from the government.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But in those days, my father explained to me more than one occasion, a transit visa was your only hope that maybe you could get out and escape.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that's where Sugihara came in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he told me, on more than one occasion, told me that, you know, word came to them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were living in the forest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were the refugees.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were Bundists.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Bundists were comrades in arms, in effect.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everything that happened anywhere in the world, there was a network of information to travel to refugees.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Refugees are well, very well-informed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "By-- by instinct, and the nature of their circumstance, they have to be to survive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they learned that this ambassador-- not ambassador, but the Council General of Japan-- was going to issue perhaps visas.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he, with so many others of course, took their life in their own hands to go to Sugihara's home, where the foreign ministry of Japan lived, existed, and milled about the courtyard-- there are many pictures of this scene that I have seen since-- pleading with Sugihara to issue them transit visas.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, oh yes, stood there, and went, and waited.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
